statement.p:
The value of \int_0^1 t\,dt, which gives the area under the curve f(t) = t^2 between t = 0 and t = 1 can be calculated using the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus. Since the integrand t^2 is continuous on the interval from t=0 to t=1 we find
\begin{aligned}[t] \int_0^1 t^2\,dt \amp= \Big(\dfrac{t^3}{3}\Big)\Big|_0^1\\ \amp= \Big(\dfrac{1^3}{3}\Big) -\Big(\dfrac{0^3}{3}\Big)\\ \int_0^1 t\,dt \amp= \dfrac{1}{3} \end{aligned}
which compares favorably with our earlier estimates.
